{"id": 223730006, "title": "Woman and two child pedestrians rushed to hospital after driver loses control of van", "text": "The incident happened in the bustling town of Dungloe in the west of the county on Saturday. A van struck a wall just off the town's Main Street just after 4.20pm. Gardai immediately sealed off the road between Greene's Corner and the town's Main Street as diversions were put in place. A woman in her 50s and a young boy and girl were caught up in the incident. They were immediately rushed to Letterkenny University Hospital for treatment. However, their injuries are not understood to be life-threatening. Garda forensic examiners were on the scene and have carried out a full examination. A small white van at the centre of the incident was loaded onto a truck and taken away for examination. A Garda spokesperson said: \"Garda\u00ed and emergency services attended the scene of a road traffic collision on Carnmore Road in Dungloe, Co Donegal, yesterday afternoon, Saturday 25th May 2024. \"The collision occurred at approximately 4:20pm and involved a van colliding with a number of pedestrians. \"The pedestrians, a woman in her 50s, a male child and a female infant were all taken from the scene to Letterkenny General Hospital to be treated for injuries believed to be non-life threatening. \"No other injuries were reported.\u201d", "summary": "<p>A woman in her 50s and two children were rushed to hospital after a van driver lost control and the vehicle struck a number of pedestrians in a Co Donegal town.</p>", "url": "https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/woman-and-two-child-pedestrians-rushed-to-hospital-after-driver-loses-control-of-van/a1140481367.html", "image": "https://focus.independent.ie/thumbor/XhHqH5BYZIaYVAKTOsgyVCnd0lI=/0x399:2954x2366/550x550/prod-mh-ireland/bb239aab-2389-407c-8dac-912c8cdb3750/3f61d9f0-1c52-4920-9da5-a8935d80505b/Dungloe%20accident2.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 14:08:41", "author": "Stephen Maguire", "authors": ["Stephen Maguire"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": -0.037}